[thinking] **Evaluating Java SecurityManager**
[thinking] 
[thinking] In Java 21, I can only set the SecurityManager if the property `java.security.manager=allow` is specified. That requires adding a JVM argument. I wonder if the native image supports the SecurityManager. There are mentions of deprecations, and it seems that `ObjectStreamClass.newInstance` may not exist in a native image. But, testing indicates that some dynamic reporting works. To be cautious, the SecurityManager may not be fully supported in the native image.
